# CURSOR IDE Rules for Mobile Development

Source: [araguaci/cursor-skills](https://github.com/araguaci/cursor-skills) — [cursor-skills.vercel.app/mobile](https://cursor-skills.vercel.app/mobile/)

Templates and examples: `.cursor/resources/araguaci-cursor-skills/mobile/`

## Overview

Rules and best practices for mobile development in Cursor. Covers React Native, Flutter, Expo, and general mobile patterns.

## Environment Setup

### Recommended extensions

- React Native Tools
- Flutter + Dart
- Expo Tools
- Mobile Development tooling
- Android Studio integration

### Standard project layout

```
project/
├── src/
├── tests/
├── docs/
├── assets/
├── android/
├── ios/
├── package.json
└── .env
```

### Mandatory requirements

- Follow mobile development principles
- Use proper error handling
- Implement testing
- Use secure communication
- Follow platform best practices

## Framework guidelines

### React Native

- Follow RN conventions for components and navigation
- Use built-in APIs and components where appropriate
- Implement navigation with a maintained library (React Navigation, Expo Router)
- Use RN testing tools (Jest, React Native Testing Library)
- Optimize lists (`FlatList`), avoid unnecessary re-renders, profile with Flipper

### Flutter

- Follow widget and state-management conventions
- Prefer composition over deep widget trees
- Use `flutter test` and integration tests
- Set `dart.flutterSdkPath` in workspace settings when needed

### Expo

- Prefer managed workflow unless bare workflow is required
- Use `expo-dev-client` for custom native code
- Follow EAS Build/Update practices for deployment
- Keep `app.json` / `app.config` consistent with native projects

## Code quality

- Consistent naming and formatting (Prettier, ESLint, `dart format`)
- Document components, APIs, deployment, and troubleshooting
- Minimum 80% test coverage target for critical paths
- Unit, integration, and E2E tests for user journeys

## Security

- Validate all inputs; sanitize before processing
- Encrypt sensitive local data; use secure storage (Keychain, Keystore)
- HTTPS for all network traffic
- Follow OWASP mobile guidelines
- Proper auth and authorization on API calls

## Performance

- Optimize images (WebP, lazy loading, caching)
- Lazy-load screens and heavy modules
- Monitor memory and bundle size
- Use platform-specific optimizations when needed
- Profile before optimizing

## Platform considerations

- Test on both iOS and Android
- Use platform-specific code only when necessary (`Platform.select`, `.ios.tsx` / `.android.tsx`)
- Follow Apple HIG and Material Design where applicable
- Test multiple screen sizes and orientations

## Deployment & CI/CD

- Environment-specific config via env vars, not hardcoded secrets
- Automate test + build in CI
- Use feature flags or staged rollouts for risky changes
- Monitor crashes and performance in production

